snippet.textDisplay: Sorry but if a GPU can't stand being pushed to 100% constantly for hours without frying itself it's the GPU vendor's fault (bad cooling, bad firmware that controls cooling and clocks, etc), not the software/game's fault. Mining crypto doesn't fry GPUs and I'm very certain that mining pushes much more the GPUs than just playing a random game. Blame whoever made that card. (Not Nvidia, I'm sure their own reference cards are fine. Blame whoever made THAT specific card's cooling and firmware like MSI, ASUS, Gigabyte etc)
